Alpine-specific hotfix: syncrepl invokes mdb's be_modrdn / be_add /
be_modify / be_delete without setting orm_no_opattrs=1, so mdb's
modrdn (and friends) call slap_mods_opattrs() which auto-injects a
"replace modifiersName=<o_dn>" mod whenever modifiersName is not
already in the modlist. Since op->o_dn is the consumer's local rootdn
(op->o_bd->be_rootdn) the consumer ends up with modifiersName=cn=consumer
instead of the provider's value.

After MR#817 removed the kludge that always forced modifiersName into
the modlist (commit 87933f3e, ITS#10250) the auto-overwrite becomes
visible whenever provider and consumer happen to already agree on
modifiersName (so syncrepl_diff_entry generates no mod for it).
Worst case the consumer ends up with the provider's entryCSN (from
the modrdn) but the wrong modifiersName, and ITS#10358's retry sees
"identical CSN" and skips remediation.

Masked on x86_64/aarch64 but reproduces deterministically on
x86/armv7/armhf/s390x. Also affects delta-multiprovider replication
(test063) flakily on ppc64le.

Two affected code paths in servers/slapd/syncrepl.c:

1. syncrepl_entry() — refresh-mode rename+content updates (be_modrdn).
   Mirrors what the parallel be_modify branch already does.

2. syncrepl_message_to_op() — delta-sync log replay (be_add, be_modify,
   be_modrdn, be_delete). Set the flag once at function entry and clear
   at the 'done:' exit so all four backend calls run with op-attr
   auto-injection suppressed.

--- a/servers/slapd/syncrepl.c
+++ b/servers/slapd/syncrepl.c
@@ -3214,6 +3214,7 @@ syncrepl_message_to_op(
 	Debug( LDAP_DEBUG_SYNC, "syncrepl_message_to_op: %s tid %p\n",
 		si->si_ridtxt, (void *)op->o_tid );

+	op->orm_no_opattrs = 1;
 	switch( op->o_tag ) {
 	case LDAP_REQ_ADD:
 	case LDAP_REQ_MODIFY:
@@ -3347,6 +3348,7 @@ syncrepl_message_to_op(
 		break;
 	}
 done:
+	op->orm_no_opattrs = 0;
 	if ( do_graduate )
 		slap_graduate_commit_csn( op );
 	if ( do_unlock )
@@ -4641,6 +4643,7 @@ retry_modrdn:;
 				mod->sml_next = m2;
 			}
 			op->o_bd = si->si_wbe;
+			op->orm_no_opattrs = 1;
 retry_modrdn:;
 			rs_reinit( &rs_modify, REP_RESULT );
 			rc = op->o_bd->be_modrdn( op, &rs_modify );
@@ -4656,6 +4659,7 @@ retry_modrdn:;
 					goto retry_modrdn;
 				}
 			}
+			op->orm_no_opattrs = 0;
 			if ( rc == LDAP_ASSERTION_FAILED ) {
 				goto retry_diff;
 			}
